snippet: Rory McIlroy birdied the 18th hole to beat Adam Scott at the Australian Open in Sydney, winning for the first time in 2013.
abstract: Rory McIlroy birdies the 18th hole to beat Adam Scott at the Australian Open in Sydney, winning for the first time in 2013 and denying Scott the triple crown of Australian golf; other golf news noted.
lead_paragraph: Rory McIlroy birdied the 18th hole to beat Adam Scott at the Australian Open in Sydney, winning for the first time in 2013.

headline.main: Birdie on 18 Lifts McIlroy at the Australian Open
